This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with meta-reinforcement learning approaches and developing learning procedures that can adapt quickly to a distribution of tasks with the help of a few examples. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for exploration strategies that uses self-supervised or supervised learning objectives for adaptation, which is a common topic in the machine learning community.

The paper could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with developing intelligent agents that can adapt to new tasks quickly. The paper's focus on exploration strategies is also relevant to the field of AI, as exploration is a critical component of many intelligent systems.

The paper could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics) as it deals with developing learning procedures that can adapt quickly to a distribution of tasks, which is a common problem in robotics. Additionally, the paper's focus on exploration strategies is relevant to the field of robotics, as exploration is a critical component of many robotic systems.
